<p>One of the environments which we know least about on Earth is, without question, the cave environment. An unknowable amount of passage still remains unmapped, itâ€™s inhabitants unseen. Cavers are generally extremely conscious of the effect our presence has upon the environment, and we try to minimise this as much as possible. But to what degree has our presence on the planet altered environments which we have not even dared to dream of yet? â€˜Wildnessâ€™ is an intrinsic draw for exploratory cavers, seeking to discover places that humanity has not thus far understood or controlled.</p>

